&lt;p&gt;The Adult Community/Primary Care Services Group is looking for a dynamic, highly motivated and experienced nurse to join the management team to support the development of services within the Group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Service Delivery Manager, it is essential that you are pro-active, adaptable and flexible to meet the needs of the service. The applicant must have evidence of excellent leadership &amp; management skill sets with experience in service development and improvement methodologies. In addition, you will clearly demonstrate commitment to and development of the Directorate to ensure all requirements of the agenda are met.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, the Trust is committed to personal and professional development; the successful applicant will receive support and training to deliver the requirements of the role, to achieve their full potential and to become a key member of the management team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jodie Winfield or Rachael Brown via PA - Kim Dean - 01902 444589, kimdean@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
